titleproper.value:
Guide to the Hudson-Fulton Celebration Collection
                    <lb/>
                    <date>1909</date>
                    <lb/>
                    <num>PR 268</num>

author.value: Finding aid prepared by Processed by Lucas Buresch

creation.value:
This finding aid was produced using the Archivists' Toolkit
                <date>2011-12-13T15:05-0500</date>

abstract.label: Abstract
abstract.value: Paintings and photographs of parade floats from the Hudson-Fulton Celebration of 1909.

p.value: Photocopying undertaken by staff only. Limited to twenty exposures of stable, unbound material per day. See guidelines in Print Room for details.
This collection should be cited as Hudson-Fulton Celebration Collection, PR 268, Department of Prints, Photographs, and Architectural Collections, The New-York Historical Society.

Also included in the celebration were naval parades with vessels from nine countries, including 53 U.S. naval vessels, fireworks, buildings and bridges illuminated with electric light, and a 63-foot replica of Hudson's 
                <title render="italic" type="simple">Half Moon</title> built in Amsterdam and sailed to New York.

The miscellaneous printed material is made up of original packaging labels from the gift, and a certificate of appreciation to General Stewart L. Woodford, President of the Hudson-Fulton Celebration Commission, from the Committee of Japanese Residents of New York commemorating the gift of 2,100 cherry trees from Japan to be planted along Riverside Drive.
